  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date federal contract obligations for NAICS 325412 total $10.7B. Award activity shows 11,516 awards with an average award size of $925K. Obligations are down 18.6% year over year. Fiscal-year history shows volatile funding: FY21 obligations were $19.5B, FY22 obligations were $34.4B, FY23 obligations were $12.8B, FY24 obligations were $10.1B, and FY25 obligations were $13.1B. The current-year total is a partial, fiscal year to date figure. Buying is highly concentrated: the Department of Veterans Affairs accounts for $9.9B of obligations, and the next-highest buyer, the Department of Health and Human Services, accounts for $562M. Vendor concentration mirrors buying concentration: MCKESSON CORPORATION received $9.9B in obligations, and other suppliers each received between $33.1M and $118M. This profile shows a market dominated by one large buyer and one large supplier in the current fiscal period, with overall obligations lower than the prior year-to-date aggregate.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What changed year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations are down 18.6% year over year. Total obligations for FY2026 to date are $10.7B compared with prior fiscal-year totals such as $13.1B in FY25 and $10.1B in FY24. The number of awards is 11,516 with an average award size of $925K, indicating continued transaction activity despite the decline in total dollars."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who dominates buying and supply in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Veterans Affairs dominates buying with $9.9B in obligations. MCKESSON CORPORATION is the dominant vendor with $9.9B in obligations, while other top vendors range from $118M to $33.1M and the next-largest buying agency is the Department of Health and Human Services at $562M."
      }
    ]
  },
